            "text": "Elevated but stable vs prior values (510, 525, 540 pg/mL over 6 months). Consistent with compensated HFrEF on quadruple GDMT in CKD3a — both impaired LVEF and reduced eGFR contribute to chronic NT-proBNP elevation. NICE NG106 ruling-in cutoff at age >=75 is 125 pg/mL; CKD3a typically adds a clearance-related elevation."
          }
        ]
      },
